      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Grill the corn (10 min): Preheat your grill or grill pan to medium-high heat. Brush the corn all over with olive oil or melted butter. Grill for 2 to 3 minutes per side, turning occasionally, until lightly charred and tender. Set aside to cool slightly.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "5 ears corn,1-2 Tablespoons olive oil",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Make the dressing (5 min): In a medium bowl, whisk together the mayo, sour cream, grated garlic, lime zest and juice, chili powder, and salt until smooth.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "1/4 cup mayonnaise,1/4 cup sour cream,1 clove garlic,1 lime,1/4 teaspoon chili powder,1 teaspoon kosher salt",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Cut and mix (5 min): Slice the kernels off the cooled corn and place them in a large mixing bowl. Add the cheese, scallions, cilantro, and jalapeño. Pour the dressing over top and toss well to coat.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "2 oz cotija cheese,1/3 cup finely sliced scallions,1/3 cup finely chopped cilantro,1 jalapeño pepper",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Finish and serve: Taste and adjust seasoning with more salt or lime, if needed. Garnish with extra cilantro and cheese. Serve warm, at room temp, or chilled.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Spin leaves dry first. Whisk dressing ingredients until thick and pourable. Dress at the table, not in the kitchen, so it stays evenly coated.",
              "cause": "Dressing not emulsified, or salad too wet.",
              "symptom": "Dressing pools at the bottom of the bowl"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Combine everything cold and dress just before serving. Sturdy leaves (kale, chicory, romaine) cope with sitting; spinach and rocket don't.",
              "cause": "Dressed too early, or fruit/cheese added warm.",
              "symptom": "Leaves wilted by the time it reached the table"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Three parts oil to one part acid is the classic ratio. Adjust with a squeeze of lemon if it's flat, or a splash more oil if it's sharp.",
              "cause": "Wrong oil-to-acid ratio in the dressing.",
              "symptom": "Salad tastes too oily"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Toss the leaves with dressing first, then scatter cheese, nuts, croutons on top. Don't toss again after garnishing.",
              "cause": "Heavy ingredients added before tossing.",
              "symptom": "Toppings ended up in the bottom"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Variations",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Add-protein: top with grilled chicken, halloumi, or a soft-boiled egg for a main-course salad.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Crunch upgrade: scatter toasted nuts or seeds on top, pumpkin, almond, sunflower.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Best fresh. Leftovers keep two days in the fridge; reheat covered with a splash of liquid.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A British home cook's dish. It sits among the recipes families remember without thinking about, the kind that gets adjusted across generations and never quite the same twice.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
